        </div>
    </div>
</div>
                        
                        <p>I refuse to believe that the four candidates in the presidential race represent the best leadership America has to offer. With a population of 324 million, the United States surely has dozens, if not hundreds or thousands of better leaders than the ones presently contending for the Oval Office. We can do better than this.</p>
<p><em>Matthew T. King is a Trinity junior. His column, “at the water's edge” runs on alternate Mondays.</em></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 14.6667px; font-family: Calibri; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: italic; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"></span></p>

